    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-21T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-21T08:00:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1816: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-21T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 21, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 21—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>148. Relative to armed clash in Manchuria between forces of China and Japan, Sir
                    Eric Drummond<note n="29" xml:id="d22fn29">Secretary-General of the League of
                        Nations.</note> could offer no unprejudiced information and he queried of me
                    whether you would furnish him with facts for his own guidance.</p>
                <p>Drummond desires to have also your opinion on the involvement of the Kellogg Pact
                    in this matter and the basis for your views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
